HEADWORD: Staggerbush
<hw>Stag"ger*bush`</hw> <pr>(-b⟦usdot⟧sh`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An American shrub (<spn>Andromeda Mariana</spn>)
having clusters of nodding white flowers. It grows in low, sandy places,
and is said to poison lambs and calves.</def>
<rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Staggeringly</ent>⟦br⟧
